"title": "5151: feet",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5151",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The part of the body associated with moving and with foundation, direction and chosen path. Feet may symbolise the response to God's direction. The feet of God and of Jesus Christ are mentioned symbolically to describe some divine characteristics.</p>\n<h2>Feet as part of the physical body</h2>\n<h3>Human feet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:19-Exod30:21\">EXO 30:19–30:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:23\">LEV 8:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:4\">DEU 8:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:9\">JOS 14:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:4\">2SA 4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:23\">1KI 15:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:1\">SNG 7:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:11\">EZK 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek25:6\">EZK 25:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44\">LUK 7:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:7\">ACT 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>The feet of creatures and objects of worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:9\">GEN 8:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:3\">EXO 37:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:7\">EZK 1:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:33\">DAN 2:33</a></p>\n<h2>A whole person may be represented by the foot</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:4\">JOB 28:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:11\">PSA 36:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:18\">PRO 6:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:7\">ISA 59:7</a></p>\n<h2>Symbolic references to human feet</h2>\n<h3>In relation to guidance, direction and following</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:5\">PSA 17:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:31\">PSA 37:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:18\">PSA 44:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:13\">PSA 56:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:101\">PSA 119:101</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:105\">PSA 119:105</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:6\">PRO 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:26-Prov4:27\">PRO 4:26–4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:79\">LUK 1:79</a></p>\n<h3>In relation to disobedience and waywardness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1\">PSA 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:22\">2KI 21:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:5\">JOB 31:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:15-Prov1:16\">PRO 1:15–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:14\">PRO 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:18\">PRO 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:7\">ISA 59:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8\">MAT 18:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:45\">MRK 9:45</a></p>\n<h3>In relation to a secure standing with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:2\">PSA 40:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:9\">1SA 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:34\">2SA 22:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:33\">PSA 18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:8\">PSA 31:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:9\">PSA 66:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:26\">PRO 4:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:19\">HAB 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:58\">1CO 15:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:13\">EPH 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>In relation to bringing the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:7\">ISA 52:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:15\">NAM 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:15\">ROM 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:15\">EPH 6:15</a></p>\n<h3>In relation to expressing attitudes and emotions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:24\">JOS 10:24</a> <em>defeat and humiliation</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:4-Ruth3:8\">RUT 3:4–3:8</a> <em>requesting marriage and redemption</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:24\">1SA 25:24</a> <em>supplication and homage</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:41\">1SA 25:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44\">LUK 7:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:5\">JHN 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:39-2Sam22:40\">2SA 22:39–22:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:38-Ps18:39\">PSA 18:38–18:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:17\">EZK 24:17</a> <em>mourning</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:14\">MAT 10:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:11\">MRK 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:5\">LUK 9:5</a> <em>scorn and a warning to those who reject God's message</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:35\">ACT 4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:25\">ACT 10:25</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:29\">HEB 10:29</a> <em>rejection</em></p>\n<h2>``Jesus' feet'' symbolises the source and place of God's grace</h2>\n<h3>Worshippers come to Jesus Christ's feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:35\">LUK 8:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:9\">MAT 28:9</a></p>\n<h3>The sinful come to Jesus Christ's feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:37-Luke7:38\">LUK 7:37–7:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:3\">JHN 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>The suffering come to Jesus Christ's feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:30\">MAT 15:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:22-Mark5:23\">MRK 5:22–5:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:18\">MAT 9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:41\">LUK 8:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:25\">MRK 7:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:25\">MAT 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:32\">JHN 11:32</a></p>\n<h3>People sit at Jesus Christ's feet to learn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:39\">LUK 10:39</a></strong> <em>It was common practice for disciples to gather around their teacher in this way.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:2\">JHN 8:2</a></p>\n<h3>Ultimately all will come to Jesus Christ's feet in worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:11\">ROM 14:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:23\">ISA 45:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:10\">PHP 2:10</a></p>\n<h2>``Feet of God'' symbolises his majestic presence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:4\">ZEC 14:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:10\">EXO 24:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:1\">ISA 66:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:3\">NAM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:35\">MAT 5:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:49\">ACT 7:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:2\">REV 10:2</a></p>\n<h3>God's feet are referred to in relation to worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:5\">PSA 99:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:7\">PSA 132:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a></p>\n<h2>``Beneath/under the feet'' to denote the defeat and subservience of enemies</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:24\">JOS 10:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:39\">2SA 22:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:3\">1KI 5:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:6\">PSA 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:5\">PSA 45:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:3\">PSA 47:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:23\">ISA 49:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:34\">LAM 3:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:3\">MAL 4:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:42-Matt22:45\">MAT 22:42–22:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:34-Acts2:36\">ACT 2:34–2:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:25-1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:25–15:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22-Eph1:23\">EPH 1:22–1:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:13\">HEB 10:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:9\">REV 3:9</a></p>",
